  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

Concept:     RLHF
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Fine-tunes LLMs using human preference comparisons
Year:        2017
Researchers: Christiano et al.
Applications:ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini alignment
Related:     PPO, reward model, preference learning

Concept:     Neural Scaling Laws
Category:    Theory
Definition:  Performance improves predictably with compute/data/parameters
Year:        2020
Researchers: Kaplan et al.
Applications:LLM development, compute planning
Related:     Chinchilla scaling, emergent abilities

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

